This paper focuses on the use of deep learning for path planning and motion control in robotic systems, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep reinforcement learning and neural networks also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The potential space applications mentioned in the abstract suggest a focus on systems and control (cs.SY), as well as computer vision (cs.CV) for navigating and mapping unknown environments.
